  "rationale": "Single hero adapted from hero-photo-overlay but re-expressed as hero-split-product on the warm light canvas the brief asks for (warm/editorial, never stock abstraction): copy column carries the one claim 'Go-to-market teams grow here.' with a Breeze/one-platform lede, the paired demo/free actions (one primary, one outline secondary), and the honest 299,000+/135+ proof beat; the counterweight media binds the real hubs platform graphic to show breadth at first glance. Asymmetric left anchor now names the media slot as its counterweight (fixes alignment-resolution + headerContext); the authored display heading renders verbatim (fixes display-heading identity). No text-on-media needed since art sits beside the copy, so treatments stay empty and every neverDo holds (sentence-case size-driven heading, light canvas, no text logos)."
